Scatter GL

Source: R/add.R, R/add_.R
e_scatter_gl.Rd

Draw scatter GL.

Usage

e_scatter_gl(
  e,
  y,
  z,
  name = NULL,
  coord_system = "geo",
  rm_x = TRUE,
  rm_y = TRUE,
  ...
)

e_scatter_gl_(
  e,
  y,
  z,
  name = NULL,
  coord_system = "geo",
  rm_x = TRUE,
  rm_y = TRUE,
  ...
)

Arguments

e

An echarts4r object as returned by e_charts or a proxy as returned by echarts4rProxy.

y, z

Column names containing y and z data.

name

name of the serie.

coord_system

Coordinate system to plot against.

rm_x, rm_y

Whether to remove x and y axis, defaults to TRUE.

...

Any other option to pass, check See Also section.

See also

Additional arguments

Examples

quakes |>
  e_charts(long) |>
  e_geo(
    roam = TRUE,
    boundingCoords = list(
      c(185, -10),
      c(165, -40)
    )
  ) |>
  e_scatter_gl(lat, depth)



# timeline
quakes$year <- rep(c("2017", "2018"), 500)

quakes |>
  group_by(year) |>
  e_charts(long, timeline = TRUE) |>
  e_geo(
    roam = TRUE,
    boundingCoords = list(
      c(185, -10),
      c(165, -40)
    )
  ) |>
  e_scatter_gl(lat, depth)
